Key Match Events: Milwaukee Brewers' Jackson Chourio hit a game-tying 398-foot home run in the eighth inning.
Brewers designated hitter Garrett Mitchell hit a two-run home run in the eighth inning, giving Milwaukee its first lead.
Mets starter Sean Manaea held Milwaukee to just two earned runs in five innings.
Mets reliever Phil Maton gave up two home runs in the eighth inning.
